WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Built compelling dashboards with R, Python, and Julia

00:00:02.800 --> 00:00:08.900
In the upcoming 1.4 release of Quarto, you'll be able to create compelling dashboards with R, Python, and Julia

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:13.100
This stock monitoring dashboard was built with fewer than 100 lines of code

00:00:13.100 --> 00:00:21.100
Dashboards are made up of rows and columns, then you arrange them in a grid, and add more advanced layers with sidebars, tabasets, and pages

00:00:21.100 --> 00:00:27.799
To demonstrate how to create a Quarto dashboard, first you start off with your YAML, your title, and format dashboard

00:00:27.799 --> 00:00:33.599
Next, you can add code, such as grid and a plot, as well as text, here's some content

00:00:33.599 --> 00:00:42.700
Next, Quarto has some nifty features that you can add, such as value boxes that highlight different numbers or icons that you want to show

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:47.799
Finally, when you're done, click render, and then your Quarto dashboard will render

